1147  //============================================================================
1148  // Method Description:
1161  template<typename dtype>
1162  NdArray<dtype> append(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<dtype>& inAppendValues, Axis inAxis)
1163  {
1164  switch (inAxis)
1165  {
1166  case Axis::NONE:
1167  {
1168  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inArray.size() + inAppendValues.size());
1169  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
1170  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(), inAppendValues.cend(), returnArray.begin() + inArray.size());
1171 
1172  return returnArray;
1173  }
1174  case Axis::ROW:
1175  {
1176  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
1177  const Shape appendShape = inAppendValues.shape();
1178  if (inShape.cols != appendShape.cols)
1179  {
1180  std::string errStr = "ERROR: append: all the input array dimensions except for the concatenation axis must match exactly";
1181  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1182  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1183  }
1184 
1185  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows + appendShape.rows, inShape.cols);
1186  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
1187  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(), inAppendValues.cend(), returnArray.begin() + inArray.size());
1188 
1189  return returnArray;
1190  }
1191  case Axis::COL:
1192  {
1193  Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
1194  const Shape appendShape = inAppendValues.shape();
1195  if (inShape.rows != appendShape.rows)
1196  {
1197  std::string errStr = "ERROR: append: all the input array dimensions except for the concatenation axis must match exactly";
1198  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1199  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1200  }
1201 
1202  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inShape.rows, inShape.cols + appendShape.cols);
1203  for (uint32 row = 0; row < returnArray.shape().rows; ++row)
1204  {
1205  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), returnArray.begin(row));
1206  std::copy(inAppendValues.cbegin(row), inAppendValues.cend(row), returnArray.begin(row) + inShape.cols);
1207  }
1208 
1209  return returnArray;
1210  }
1211  default:
1212  {
1213  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
1214  // of the compiler warning.
1215  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
1216  }
1217  }
1218  }

1220  //============================================================================
1221  // Method Description:
1240  template<typename dtype>
1241  NdArray<dtype> arange(dtype inStart, dtype inStop, dtype inStep)
1242  {
1243  if (inStep > 0 && inStop < inStart)
1244  {
1245  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: stop value must be larger than the start value for positive step.";
1246  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1247  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1248  }
1249 
1250  if (inStep < 0 && inStop > inStart)
1251  {
1252  std::string errStr = "ERROR: arange: start value must be larger than the stop value for negative step.";
1253  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1254  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1255  }
1256 
1257  std::vector<dtype> values;
1258 
1259  dtype theValue = inStart;
1260 
1261  if (inStep > 0)
1262  {
1263  while (theValue < inStop)
1264  {
1265  values.push_back(theValue);
1266  theValue += inStep;
1267  }
1268  }
1269  else
1270  {
1271  while (theValue > inStop)
1272  {
1273  values.push_back(theValue);
1274  theValue += inStep;
1275  }
1276  }
1277 
1278  return NdArray<dtype>(values);
1279  }

1309 
1310  return arange<dtype>(0, inStop, 1);

1830  // Method Description:
1841  template<typename dtype>
1842  NdArray<double> average(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const NdArray<dtype>& inWeights, Axis inAxis)
1843  {
1844  switch (inAxis)
1845  {
1846  case Axis::NONE:
1847  {
1848  if (inWeights.shape() != inArray.shape())
1849  {
1850  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weight values are not consistant.";
1851  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1852  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1853  }
1854 
1855  NdArray<double> weightedArray(inArray.shape());
1856  std::transform(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), inWeights.cbegin(),
1857  weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1858 
1859  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0));
1860  NdArray<double> returnArray = { sum /= inWeights.template sum<double>().item() };
1861 
1862  return returnArray;
1863  }
1864  case Axis::COL:
1865  {
1866  const Shape arrayShape = inArray.shape();
1867  if (inWeights.size() != arrayShape.cols)
1868  {
1869  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weights value are not consistant.";
1870  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1871  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1872  }
1873 
1874  double weightSum = inWeights.template sum<double>().item();
1875  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, arrayShape.rows);
1876  for (uint32 row = 0; row < arrayShape.rows; ++row)
1877  {
1878  NdArray<double> weightedArray(1, arrayShape.cols);
1879  std::transform(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), inWeights.cbegin(),
1880  weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1881 
1882  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0));
1883  returnArray(0, row) = sum / weightSum;
1884  }
1885 
1886  return returnArray;
1887  }
1888  case Axis::ROW:
1889  {
1890  if (inWeights.size() != inArray.shape().rows)
1891  {
1892  std::string errStr = "ERROR: average: input array and weight values are not consistant.";
1893  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1894  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1895  }
1896 
1897  NdArray<dtype> transposedArray = inArray.transpose();
1898 
1899  const Shape transShape = transposedArray.shape();
1900  double weightSum = inWeights.template sum<double>().item();
1901  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, transShape.rows);
1902  for (uint32 row = 0; row < transShape.rows; ++row)
1903  {
1904  NdArray<double> weightedArray(1, transShape.cols);
1905  std::transform(transposedArray.cbegin(row), transposedArray.cend(row), inWeights.cbegin(),
1906  weightedArray.begin(), std::multiplies<double>());
1907 
1908  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(weightedArray.begin(), weightedArray.end(), 0.0));
1909  returnArray(0, row) = sum / weightSum;
1910  }
1911 
1912  return returnArray;
1913  }
1914  default:
1915  {
1916  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
1917  // of the compiler warning.
1918  return NdArray<double>(0);
1919  }
1920  }
1921  }

1940  // Method Description:
1957  template<typename dtype>
1958  NdArray<dtype> bincount(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, uint16 inMinLength)
1959  {
1960  // only works with integer input types
1961  static_assert(DtypeInfo<dtype>::isInteger(), "ERROR: bincount: can only use with integer types.");
1962 
1963  dtype maxValue = inArray.max().item();
1964  if (maxValue < 0)
1965  {
1966  // no positive values so just return an empty array
1967  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
1968  }
1969 
1970  if (maxValue + 1 > DtypeInfo<dtype>::max())
1971  {
1972  std::string errStr = "Error: bincount: array values too large, will result in gigantic array that will take up alot of memory...";
1973  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
1974  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
1975  }
1976 
1977  const uint16 outArraySize = std::max(static_cast<uint16>(maxValue + 1), inMinLength);
1978  NdArray<dtype> clippedArray = inArray.clip(0, maxValue);
1979 
1980  NdArray<dtype> outArray(1, outArraySize);
1981  outArray.zeros();
1982  for (auto value : clippedArray)
1983  {
1984  ++outArray[value];
1985  }
1986 
1987  return outArray;
1988  }

2244  // Method Description:
2254  template<typename dtype>
2255  NdArray<dtype> column_stack(const std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >& inArrayList)
2256  {
2257  // first loop through to calculate the final size of the array
2258  Shape finalShape;
2259  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
2260  {
2261  if (finalShape.isnull())
2262  {
2263  finalShape = ndarray.shape();
2264  }
2265  else if (ndarray.shape().rows != finalShape.rows)
2266  {
2267  std::string errStr = "ERROR: column_stack: input arrays must have the same number of rows.";
2268  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
2269  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
2270  }
2271  else
2272  {
2273  finalShape.cols += ndarray.shape().cols;
2274  }
2275  }
2276 
2277  // now that we know the final size, contruct the output array
2278  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(finalShape);
2279  uint32 colStart = 0;
2280  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
2281  {
2282  const Shape theShape = ndarray.shape();
2283  for (uint32 row = 0; row < theShape.rows; ++row)
2284  {
2285  for (uint32 col = 0; col < theShape.cols; ++col)
2286  {
2287  returnArray(row, colStart + col) = ndarray(row, col);
2288  }
2289  }
2290  colStart += theShape.cols;
2291  }
2292 
2293  return returnArray;
2294  }

4176  // Method Description:
4187  template<typename dtype>
4188  NdArray<double> gradient(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, Axis inAxis)
4189  {
4190  switch (inAxis)
4191  {
4192  case Axis::ROW:
4193  {
4194  const auto inShape = inArray.shape();
4195  if (inShape.rows < 2)
4196  {
4197  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 row.";
4198  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4199  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4200  }
4201 
4202  // first do the first and last rows
4203  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(inShape);
4204  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
4205  {
4206  returnArray(0, col) = static_cast<double>(inArray(1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(0, col));
4207  returnArray(-1, col) = static_cast<double>(inArray(-1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(-2, col));
4208  }
4209 
4210  // then rip through the rest of the array
4211  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols; ++col)
4212  {
4213  for (uint32 row = 1; row < inShape.rows - 1; ++row)
4214  {
4215  returnArray(row, col) = (static_cast<double>(inArray(row + 1, col)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row - 1, col))) / 2.0;
4216  }
4217  }
4218 
4219  return returnArray;
4220  }
4221  case Axis::COL:
4222  {
4223  const auto inShape = inArray.shape();
4224  if (inShape.cols < 2)
4225  {
4226  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 columns.";
4227  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4228  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4229  }
4230 
4231  // first do the first and last columns
4232  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(inShape);
4233  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
4234  {
4235  returnArray(row, 0) = static_cast<double>(inArray(row, 1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, 0));
4236  returnArray(row, -1) = static_cast<double>(inArray(row, -1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, -2));
4237  }
4238 
4239  // then rip through the rest of the array
4240  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
4241  {
4242  for (uint32 col = 1; col < inShape.cols - 1; ++col)
4243  {
4244  returnArray(row, col) = (static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col + 1)) - static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col - 1))) / 2.0;
4245  }
4246  }
4247 
4248  return returnArray;
4249  }
4250  default:
4251  {
4252  // will return the gradient of the flattened array
4253  if (inArray.size() < 2)
4254  {
4255  std::string errStr = "ERROR: gradient: input array must have more than 1 element.";
4256  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4257  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4258  }
4259 
4260  auto returnArray = NdArray<double>(1, inArray.size());
4261  returnArray[0] = static_cast<double>(inArray[1]) - static_cast<double>(inArray[0]);
4262  returnArray[-1] = static_cast<double>(inArray[-1]) - static_cast<double>(inArray[-2]);
4263 
4264  std::transform(inArray.cbegin() + 2, inArray.cend(), inArray.cbegin(), returnArray.begin() + 1,
4265  [](dtype value1, dtype value2) noexcept -> double { return (static_cast<double>(value1) - static_cast<double>(value2)) / 2.0; });
4266 
4267  return returnArray;
4268  }
4269  }

4309  // Method Description:
4321  template<typename dtype>
4322  std::pair<NdArray<uint32>, NdArray<double> > histogram(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, uint32 inNumBins)
4323  {
4324  if (inNumBins == 0)
4325  {
4326  std::string errStr = "ERROR: histogram: number of bins must be positive.";
4327  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4328  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4329  }
4330 
4331  NdArray<uint32> histo = zeros<uint32>(1, inNumBins);
4332 
4333  const bool useEndPoint = true;
4334  NdArray<double> binEdges = linspace(static_cast<double>(inArray.min().item()),
4335  static_cast<double>(inArray.max().item()), inNumBins + 1, useEndPoint);
4336 
4337  for (uint32 i = 0; i < inArray.size(); ++i)
4338  {
4339  // binary search to find the bin idx
4340  const bool keepSearching = true;
4341  uint32 lowIdx = 0;
4342  uint32 highIdx = binEdges.size() - 1;
4343  while (keepSearching)
4344  {
4345  const uint32 idx = (lowIdx + highIdx) / 2; // integer division
4346  if (lowIdx == highIdx || lowIdx == highIdx - 1)
4347  {
4348  // we found the bin
4349  ++histo[lowIdx];
4350  break;
4351  }
4352 
4353  if (inArray[i] > binEdges[idx])
4354  {
4355  lowIdx = idx;
4356  }
4357  else if (inArray[i] < binEdges[idx])
4358  {
4359  highIdx = idx;
4360  }
4361  else
4362  {
4363  // we found the bin
4364  ++histo[idx];
4365  break;
4366  }
4367  }
4368  }
4369 
4370  return std::make_pair(histo, binEdges);
4371  }

4490  // Method Description:
4507  template<typename dtype>
4508  NdArray<dtype> interp(const NdArray<dtype>& inX, const NdArray<dtype>& inXp, const NdArray<dtype>& inFp)
4509  {
4510  // do some error checking first
4511  if (inXp.size() != inFp.size())
4512  {
4513  std::string errStr = "ERROR: interp: inXp and inFp need to be the same size().";
4514  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4515  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4516  }
4517 
4518  if (inX.min().item() < inXp.min().item() || inX.max().item() > inXp.max().item())
4519  {
4520  std::string errStr = "ERROR: interp: endpoints of inX should be contained within inXp.";
4521  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4522  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4523  }
4524 
4525  // sort the input inXp and inFp data
4526  NdArray<uint32> sortedXpIdxs = argsort(inXp);
4527  NdArray<dtype> sortedXp(1, inFp.size());
4528  NdArray<dtype> sortedFp(1, inFp.size());
4529  uint32 counter = 0;
4530  for (auto sortedXpIdx : sortedXpIdxs)
4531  {
4532  sortedXp[counter] = inXp[sortedXpIdx];
4533  sortedFp[counter++] = inFp[sortedXpIdx];
4534  }
4535 
4536  // sort the input inX array
4537  NdArray<dtype> sortedX = sort(inX);
4538 
4539  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inX.size());
4540 
4541  uint32 currXpIdx = 0;
4542  uint32 currXidx = 0;
4543  while (currXidx < sortedX.size())
4544  {
4545  if (sortedXp[currXpIdx] <= sortedX[currXidx] && sortedX[currXidx] <= sortedXp[currXpIdx + 1])
4546  {
4547  const double percent = static_cast<double>(sortedX[currXidx] - sortedXp[currXpIdx]) /
4548  static_cast<double>(sortedXp[currXpIdx + 1] - sortedXp[currXpIdx]);
4549  returnArray[currXidx++] = utils::interp(sortedFp[currXpIdx], sortedFp[currXpIdx + 1], percent);
4550  }
4551  else
4552  {
4553  ++currXpIdx;
4554  }
4555  }
4556 
4557  return returnArray;
4558  }

4884  NdArray<dtype> linspace(dtype inStart, dtype inStop, uint32 inNum, bool endPoint)
4885  {
4886  if (inNum == 0)
4887  {
4888  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
4889  }
4890  else if (inNum == 1)
4891  {
4892  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart };
4893  return returnArray;
4894  }
4895 
4896  if (inStop <= inStart)
4897  {
4898  std::string errStr = "ERROR: linspace: stop value must be greater than the start value.";
4899  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
4900  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
4901  }
4902 
4903  if (endPoint)
4904  {
4905  if (inNum == 2)
4906  {
4907  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart, inStop };
4908  return returnArray;
4909  }
4910  else
4911  {
4912  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inNum);
4913  returnArray[0] = inStart;
4914  returnArray[inNum - 1] = inStop;
4915 
4916  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / (inNum - 1);
4917  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inNum - 1; ++i)
4918  {
4919  returnArray[i] = returnArray[i - 1] + step;
4920  }
4921 
4922  return returnArray;
4923  }
4924  }
4925  else
4926  {
4927  if (inNum == 2)
4928  {
4929  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / (inNum);
4930  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = { inStart, inStart + step };
4931  return returnArray;
4932  }
4933  else
4934  {
4935  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inNum);
4936  returnArray[0] = inStart;
4937 
4938  dtype step = (inStop - inStart) / inNum;
4939  for (uint32 i = 1; i < inNum; ++i)
4940  {
4941  returnArray[i] = returnArray[i - 1] + step;
4942  }
4943 
4944  return returnArray;
4945  }
4946  }

5616  //============================================================================
5617  // Method Description:
5628  template<typename dtype>
5629  NdArray<double> nanmean(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, Axis inAxis)
5630  {
5631  switch (inAxis)
5632  {
5633  case Axis::NONE:
5634  {
5635  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), 0.0,
5636  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) noexcept -> dtype { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + inValue2; }));
5637 
5638  const double numberNonNan = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cend(), 0.0,
5639  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) noexcept -> dtype { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + 1; }));
5640 
5641  NdArray<double> returnArray = { sum /= numberNonNan };
5642 
5643  return returnArray;
5644  }
5645  case Axis::COL:
5646  {
5647  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
5648  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5649  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5650  {
5651  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), 0.0,
5652  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) noexcept -> dtype { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + inValue2; }));
5653 
5654  double numberNonNan = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row), 0.0,
5655  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) noexcept -> dtype { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + 1; }));
5656 
5657  returnArray(0, row) = sum / numberNonNan;
5658  }
5659 
5660  return returnArray;
5661  }
5662  case Axis::ROW:
5663  {
5664  NdArray<dtype> transposedArray = inArray.transpose();
5665  const Shape transShape = transposedArray.shape();
5666  NdArray<double> returnArray(1, transShape.rows);
5667  for (uint32 row = 0; row < transShape.rows; ++row)
5668  {
5669  double sum = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(transposedArray.cbegin(row), transposedArray.cend(row), 0.0,
5670  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) noexcept -> dtype { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + inValue2; }));
5671 
5672  double numberNonNan = static_cast<double>(std::accumulate(transposedArray.cbegin(row), transposedArray.cend(row), 0.0,
5673  [](dtype inValue1, dtype inValue2) noexcept -> dtype { return std::isnan(inValue2) ? inValue1 : inValue1 + 1; }));
5674 
5675  returnArray(0, row) = sum / numberNonNan;
5676  }

5805  // Method Description:
5817  template<typename dtypeOut = double, typename dtype>
5818  NdArray<double> nanpercentile(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, double inPercentile,
5819  Axis inAxis, const std::string& inInterpMethod)
5820  {
5821  if (inPercentile < 0.0 || inPercentile > 100.0)
5822  {
5823  std::string errStr = "ERROR: percentile: input percentile value must be of the range [0, 100].";
5824  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
5825  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
5826  }
5827 
5828  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") != 0 &&
5829  inInterpMethod.compare("lower") != 0 &&
5830  inInterpMethod.compare("higher") != 0 &&
5831  inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") != 0 &&
5832  inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") != 0)
5833  {
5834  std::string errStr = "ERROR: percentile: input interpolation method is not a vaid option.\n";
5835  errStr += "\tValid options are 'linear', 'lower', 'higher', 'nearest', 'midpoint'.";
5836  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
5837  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
5838  }
5839 
5840  switch (inAxis)
5841  {
5842  case Axis::NONE:
5843  {
5844  if (utils::essentiallyEqual(inPercentile, 0.0))
5845  {
5846  for (auto value : inArray)
5847  {
5848  if (!isnan(value))
5849  {
5850  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(value) };
5851  return returnArray;
5852  }
5853  }
5854  return NdArray<dtypeOut>(0);
5855  }
5856  else if (utils::essentiallyEqual(inPercentile, 100.0))
5857  {
5858  for (int32 i = static_cast<int32>(inArray.size()) - 1; i > -1; --i)
5859  {
5860  if (!isnan(inArray[i]))
5861  {
5862  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(inArray[i]) };
5863  return returnArray;
5864  }
5865  }
5866  return NdArray<dtypeOut>(0);
5867  }
5868 
5869  std::vector<double> arrayCopy;
5870  uint32 numNonNan = 0;
5871  for (auto value : inArray)
5872  {
5873  if (!isnan(value))
5874  {
5875  arrayCopy.push_back(value);
5876  ++numNonNan;
5877  }
5878  }
5879 
5880  if (arrayCopy.size() < 2)
5881  {
5882  return NdArray<dtypeOut>(0);
5883  }
5884 
5885  const int32 i = static_cast<int32>(std::floor(static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1) * inPercentile / 100.0));
5886  const uint32 indexLower = static_cast<uint32>(clip<uint32>(i, 0, numNonNan - 2));
5887 
5888  std::sort(arrayCopy.begin(), arrayCopy.end());
5889 
5890  if (inInterpMethod.compare("linear") == 0)
5891  {
5892  const double percentI = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5893  const double fraction = (inPercentile / 100.0 - percentI) /
5894  (static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1) - percentI);
5895 
5896  const double returnValue = arrayCopy[indexLower] + (arrayCopy[indexLower + 1] - arrayCopy[indexLower]) * fraction;
5897  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(returnValue) };
5898  return returnArray;
5899  }
5900  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("lower") == 0)
5901  {
5902  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower]) };
5903  return returnArray;
5904  }
5905  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("higher") == 0)
5906  {
5907  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) };
5908  return returnArray;
5909  }
5910  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("nearest") == 0)
5911  {
5912  const double percent = inPercentile / 100.0;
5913  const double percent1 = static_cast<double>(indexLower) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5914  const double percent2 = static_cast<double>(indexLower + 1) / static_cast<double>(numNonNan - 1);
5915  const double diff1 = percent - percent1;
5916  const double diff2 = percent2 - percent;
5917 
5918  switch (argmin<double>({ diff1, diff2 }).item())
5919  {
5920  case 0:
5921  {
5922  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower]) };
5923  return returnArray;
5924  }
5925  case 1:
5926  {
5927  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>(arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) };
5928  return returnArray;
5929  }
5930  }
5931  }
5932  else if (inInterpMethod.compare("midpoint") == 0)
5933  {
5934  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { (arrayCopy[indexLower] + arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) / 2.0 };
5935  return returnArray;
5936  }
5937  }
5938  case Axis::COL:
5939  {
5940  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
5941 
5942  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5943  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5944  {
5945  NdArray<dtypeOut> outValue = nanpercentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row)),
5946  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod);
5947 
5948  if (outValue.size() == 1)
5949  {
5950  returnArray[row] = outValue.item();
5951  }
5952  else
5953  {
5954  returnArray[row] = constants::nan;
5955  }
5956  }
5957 
5958  return returnArray;
5959  }
5960  case Axis::ROW:
5961  {
5962  NdArray<dtype> arrayTrans = inArray.transpose();
5963  const Shape inShape = arrayTrans.shape();
5964 
5965  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
5966  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
5967  {
5968  NdArray<dtypeOut> outValue = nanpercentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(arrayTrans.cbegin(row), arrayTrans.cend(row)),
5969  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod);
5970 
5971  if (outValue.size() == 1)
5972  {
5973  returnArray[row] = outValue.item();
5974  }
5975  else
5976  {
5977  returnArray[row] = constants::nan;
5978  }
5979  }
5980 
5981  return returnArray;
5982  }
5983  default:
5984  {
5985  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
5986  // of the compiler warning.
5987  return NdArray<dtypeOut>(0);
5988  }
5989  }
5990  }

6583  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray = { static_cast<dtypeOut>((arrayCopy[indexLower] + arrayCopy[indexLower + 1]) / 2.0) };
6584  return returnArray;
6585  }
6586  }
6587  case Axis::COL:
6588  {
6589  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
6590 
6591  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6592  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6593  {
6594  returnArray[row] = percentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(inArray.cbegin(row), inArray.cend(row)),
6595  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod).item();
6596  }
6597 
6598  return returnArray;
6599  }
6600  case Axis::ROW:
6601  {
6602  NdArray<dtype> arrayTrans = inArray.transpose();
6603  const Shape inShape = arrayTrans.shape();
6604 
6605  NdArray<dtypeOut> returnArray(1, inShape.rows);
6606  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
6607  {
6608  returnArray[row] = percentile<dtypeOut>(NdArray<dtype>(arrayTrans.cbegin(row), arrayTrans.cend(row)),
6609  inPercentile, Axis::NONE, inInterpMethod).item();
6610  }
6611 
6612  return returnArray;
6613  }
6614  default:
6615  {
6616  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
6617  // of the compiler warning.
6618  return NdArray<dtypeOut>(0);
6619  }
6620  }
6621  }

7260  // Method Description:
7272  template<typename dtype>
7273  NdArray<dtype> roll(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, int32 inShift, Axis inAxis)
7274  {
7275  switch (inAxis)
7276  {
7277  case Axis::NONE:
7278  {
7279  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inArray.size();
7280  if (inShift > 0)
7281  {
7282  shift = inArray.size() - shift;
7283  }
7284 
7285  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inArray);
7286  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(), returnArray.begin() + shift, returnArray.end());
7287 
7288  return returnArray;
7289  }
7290  case Axis::COL:
7291  {
7292  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
7293 
7294  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inShape.cols;
7295  if (inShift > 0)
7296  {
7297  shift = inShape.cols - shift;
7298  }
7299 
7300  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(inArray);
7301  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.rows; ++row)
7302  {
7303  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(row), returnArray.begin(row) + shift, returnArray.end(row));
7304  }
7305 
7306  return returnArray;
7307  }
7308  case Axis::ROW:
7309  {
7310  const Shape inShape = inArray.shape();
7311 
7312  uint32 shift = std::abs(inShift) % inShape.rows;
7313  if (inShift > 0)
7314  {
7315  shift = inShape.rows - shift;
7316  }
7317 
7318  NdArray<dtype> returnArray = inArray.transpose();
7319  for (uint32 row = 0; row < inShape.cols; ++row)
7320  {
7321  std::rotate(returnArray.begin(row), returnArray.begin(row) + shift, returnArray.end(row));
7322  }
7323 
7324  return returnArray.transpose();
7325  }
7326  default:
7327  {
7328  // this isn't actually possible, just putting this here to get rid
7329  // of the compiler warning.
7330  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
7331  }
7332  }
7333  }

7407  //============================================================================
7408  // Method Description:
7417  template<typename dtype>
7418  NdArray<dtype> row_stack(const std::initializer_list<NdArray<dtype> >& inArrayList)
7419  {
7420  // first loop through to calculate the final size of the array
7421  Shape finalShape;
7422  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
7423  {
7424  if (finalShape.isnull())
7425  {
7426  finalShape = ndarray.shape();
7427  }
7428  else if (ndarray.shape().cols != finalShape.cols)
7429  {
7430  std::string errStr = "ERROR: row_stack: input arrays must have the same number of columns.";
7431  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
7432  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
7433  }
7434  else
7435  {
7436  finalShape.rows += ndarray.shape().rows;
7437  }
7438  }
7439 
7440  // now that we know the final size, contruct the output array
7441  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(finalShape);
7442  uint32 rowStart = 0;
7443  for (auto& ndarray : inArrayList)
7444  {
7445  const Shape theShape = ndarray.shape();
7446  for (uint32 row = 0; row < theShape.rows; ++row)
7447  {
7448  for (uint32 col = 0; col < theShape.cols; ++col)
7449  {
7450  returnArray(rowStart + row, col) = ndarray(row, col);
7451  }
7452  }
7453  rowStart += theShape.rows;
7454  }
7455 
7456  return returnArray;
7457  }

7476  std::set<dtype> in1(inArray1.cbegin(), inArray1.cend());

7480  in2.begin(), in2.end(), res.begin());

7482  return NdArray<dtype>(res);

8100  NdArray<double> trapz(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, double dx, Axis inAxis)
8101  {

8103  switch (inAxis)
8104  {
8105  case Axis::COL:
8106  {
8107  NdArray<double> returnArray(inShape.rows, 1);

8111  for (uint32 col = 0; col < inShape.cols - 1; ++col)
8112  {
8113  sum += static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col + 1) - inArray(row, col)) / 2.0 +
8114  static_cast<double>(inArray(row, col));
8115  }
8116 
8117  returnArray[row] = sum * dx;

8119

8132  sum += static_cast<double>(arrayTranspose(row, col + 1) - arrayTranspose(row, col)) / 2.0 +
8133  static_cast<double>(arrayTranspose(row, col));
8134  }
8135 
8136  returnArray[row] = sum * dx;
8137  }
8138 
8139  return returnArray;

8461  // Method Description:
8472  template<typename dtype>
8473  NdArray<dtype> trim_zeros(const NdArray<dtype>& inArray, const std::string inTrim)
8474  {
8475  if (inTrim == "f")
8476  {
8477  uint32 place = 0;
8478  for (auto value : inArray)
8479  {
8480  if (value != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8481  {
8482  break;
8483  }
8484  else
8485  {
8486  ++place;
8487  }
8488  }
8489 
8490  if (place == inArray.size())
8491  {
8492  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8493  }
8494 
8495  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, inArray.size() - place);
8496  std::copy(inArray.cbegin() + place, inArray.cend(), returnArray.begin());
8497 
8498  return returnArray;
8499  }
8500  else if (inTrim == "b")
8501  {
8502  uint32 place = inArray.size();
8503  for (uint32 i = inArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i)
8504  {
8505  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8506  {
8507  break;
8508  }
8509  else
8510  {
8511  --place;
8512  }
8513  }
8514 
8515  if (place == 0 || (place == 1 && inArray[0] == 0))
8516  {
8517  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8518  }
8519 
8520  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, place);
8521  std::copy(inArray.cbegin(), inArray.cbegin() + place, returnArray.begin());
8522 
8523  return returnArray;
8524  }
8525  else if (inTrim == "fb")
8526  {
8527  uint32 placeBegin = 0;
8528  for (auto value : inArray)
8529  {
8530  if (value != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8531  {
8532  break;
8533  }
8534  else
8535  {
8536  ++placeBegin;
8537  }
8538  }
8539 
8540  if (placeBegin == inArray.size())
8541  {
8542  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8543  }
8544 
8545  uint32 placeEnd = inArray.size();
8546  for (uint32 i = inArray.size() - 1; i > 0; --i)
8547  {
8548  if (inArray[i] != static_cast<dtype>(0))
8549  {
8550  break;
8551  }
8552  else
8553  {
8554  --placeEnd;
8555  }
8556  }
8557 
8558  if (placeEnd == 0 || (placeEnd == 1 && inArray[0] == 0))
8559  {
8560  return NdArray<dtype>(0);
8561  }
8562 
8563  NdArray<dtype> returnArray(1, placeEnd - placeBegin);
8564  std::copy(inArray.cbegin() + placeBegin, inArray.cbegin() + placeEnd, returnArray.begin());
8565 
8566  return returnArray;
8567  }
8568  else
8569  {
8570  std::string errStr = "ERROR: trim_zeros: trim options are 'f' = front, 'b' = back, 'fb' = front and back.";
8571  std::cerr << errStr << std::endl;
8572  throw std::invalid_argument(errStr);
8573  }
8574  }
